  "body": "# 🚀 Feature Request\r\n\r\n### Description\r\nToday migration routines are executed under a DB transaction from a common code. Running bigger transactions will most likely cause OOMs for stakers on limited boxes. This make large migrations routines to peak memory and create problems. \r\nAdd stats to migration.\r\n\r\n### Describe the solution you'd like\r\nEvery migration routine needs to manage its own transaction. This will make the routine responsible for managing transactions and may be parallelize the migration too.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Describe alternatives you've considered\r\n\r\n<!-- ✍️--> Have you considered any alternative solutions or workarounds?\r\n\r\n\r\n### More context\r\n_Originally posted by @nisdas in https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/pull/9155#discussion_r675386912_",
